        <prompt>How did the Spanish Flu pandemic specifically affect India?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It had minimal impact due to British protection</option>
            <option letter="b">It caused the highest death toll of any country</option>
            <option letter="c">It only affected urban areas</option>
            <option letter="d">It strengthened the healthcare system</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>India suffered the highest death toll globally from the Spanish Flu, with 17-18 million deaths, exacerbated by British colonial policies, drought, and poor healthcare infrastructure.</explanation>
